  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (cb925b1 2022-11-21T00:09:19.970948Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge init\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI've used `forge init` several times before, but when I just ran `foundryup` to update to the latest version and tried to init a new project I got the following error:\r\n```\r\nforge init foobar\r\nInitializing /dev/eth/foobar...\r\nInstalling forge-std in \"/dev/eth/foobar/lib/forge-std\" (url: Some(\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/forge-std\"), tag: None)\r\nError:\r\nfatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git\r\n```",
